<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-62-0100 </DOCNO><TEXT>A method for synthesizing hydrocarbons from a methane source is describedwhich comprises: (a) contacting at a temperature within the range ofabout 500{sup 0}-1000{sup 0}C, a gas comprising methane and a solid comprisinga reducible oxide of Pr, the contacting producing C/sub 2/+hydrocarbons,coproduct water and solids comprising a reduced Pr oxide, and the contactingbeing carried out in the substantial absence of catalytically effectiveNi, Rh, Pd, Ag, Os, Ir, Pt, Au and compounds thereof; (b) recoveringC/sub 2/+hydrocarbons; (c) at least periodically contacting the solidscomprising reduced Pr oxide with an oxygen-containing gas to producea solid comprising a reducible Pr oxide; and (d) contacting a gas comprisingmethane with the solids produced in step (c) as recited in step (a).</TEXT></DOC>